==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Water deer
<hw>Wa"ter deer`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>A small Chinese deer (<spn>Hydropotes inermis</spn>). Both sexes
are destitute of antlers, but the male has large, descending canine
tusks.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The water chevrotain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Water deerlet</ent>⟦br⟧
